text: warning âš ï¸ soliloquy ahead: today marks the end of the absolutely brilliant run of @mingheartsâ€™s #usualgirls at @roundaboutnyc. ming, @tynerafaeli & @midoriglory (and @alidnyc!), i have tried to properly put into words what this show has meant to me, but never have the words felt quite adequate. when i read this play for the first time a couple years ago, i felt understood. when i saw the reading a year ago courtesy of @maggieburrows, i felt shaken to my core. it just so happens that that reading took place only weeks after the rise of the #metoo movement...and what iâ€™ve realized since then â€” which was confirmed for me in seeing this production (twice) last month â€” is that this show, mingâ€™s words, midoriâ€™s courage, and the stories being told...have unlocked something in me. this show helped me reflect back on growing up as a girl and becoming a woman in a way that i didnâ€™t realize i desperately needed. it has shone a light on small traumas i didnâ€™t quite know how to articulate, and it has given me the strength to talk openly about how weird and confusing it can be to interact with boys and men at any age. it has given me the confidence to dig into the gray area that weâ€™re all dealing with each and every single day, and i genuinely think i was able to properly express my feelings about kavanaugh because of this show. so, as 2018 comes to a close, i just have to say how eternally grateful i am to the incredible artists â€” writers, creators, visionaries â€” in our community who are pushing the boundaries. who arenâ€™t afraid to potentially shock or offend. who are willing to speak up when others would stay quiet. our world may continue to feel like a pretty scary place, but this kind of work makes me believe that we have to be doing something right. itâ€™s incredible to be reminded, time and time again, that art really does matter â¤ï¸ #offbroadway #theater #newyork #bestof2018 #artmatters #timesup #feministaf

text:
we would like to begin by saying thank you! thank you to all of the people who have donated to us, fundraised for us, sent us their art, lent us a hand, supported us from far and stood beside us through it all. we are honoured to continue our work in 2019. 
the dandelion initiative is a small team of our founder and e.d, viktoria belle and our dedicated board of directors and community volunteers. with little resources and capacity we have been able to create small change and big impact in the lives of many in our community. 
in 2018 we incorporated as a not for profit, we participated in a lot of advocacy and held some important events like our #nowwhat panel and #communitycares market. our safer bars + spaces training is continuing to work to transform food and hospitality workplace culture. our executive director has worked tirelessly to write and develop anti-harassment and violence policies for organizations to youth camps. we fought to shine a light on violence and those who perpetrate that harm. we lobbied against policies that further put women/feminized people at risk and we led important discussions across ontario through partner organizations. from montreal to thunder bay we put our experiences, stories, work and hearts on the front lines. we held many survivor centric workshops with incredible community facilitators, from resiliency, self care, art as activism, trauma and wellness, we prioritized creating safer spaces for survivors to come together and we have provided over 100 survivors with individual support in 2018. 
we did this all with just the donations we receive, the revenue from our training and the fierce dedication of our founder and executive director and our remarkable board of directors.. and you. you all have carried us with you and continue to empower us to keep doing the important work we do. 
we love you and thank you from the bottom of our hearts. may we continue to resist and thrive together in 2019. we will be taking a short break until december 28th. 
if you need support the toronto rape crisis centre/multicultural women against rape crisis line: 416-597-8808
#communitcares #metoo #timesup #ordersup #survivorsthrive

text:
if you look closely behind the caption "hard work sucks" you'll see little boxes, one has a picture of me, the next one has a quote. they alternate for a whiiiilleee.

for one entire calendar year i did a video series called "the daily dose" i created videos every single day to become more "consistent" or so i told myself. well guess what...i achieved it. i achieved consistency. it was hard fuggin work doing a video every day, cataloging, finding ideas, storing content...hard fugfing work. do you know what my result from it was...you guessed it, whatever i asked for....consistency. i achieved my goal...but what did i really want??? beneath the topline message i was delivering...i wanted to create a larger audience!!! i expended all this "hard work" and achieved my result but i didnt get what i really wanted...a larger audience. i lied to myself and i used hard work to convince myself that it would equate to a result that i wanted. hard work (alone) sucks balls backwards.

your hard work must be inspired by what you want!!! for those that think the issue was honesty... you're right but it was a level deeper than simply honesty...if i had sat down, and developed a strategy, i would have uncovered what i really wanted. your hard work...needs to be inspired...which means it needs a strategy!!! if you endeavor in "hard work" alone it will produce a result...but is that the result you want? and even if you did know "what you wanted" who is helping you get there? a strategy includes, identifying what i want, who will help, how it will help me produce my ultimate goal...and the list....goes...on. i had no idea i was lost until i just stopped one day...and looked up and said man...so much time gone. but without crying over spilled milk i realized what i really wanted...to start being honest with myself.

the greatest gift i was given was not a larger audience, or a greater outcome...it was the muthafuggin truth!!! amen to the truth. now that truth was that...i started developing a strategy!

need help developing a strategy?

hit me up about firestarter training!!!
.
.
.
.
#artist #motivation #beyou #storytelling #dopeaf #inspiration #women #metoo #fuegi #inferno

text:
2018
this has been one of the most difficult years iâ€™ve ever had the displeasure of experiencing.
from my multiple suicide attempts, hospitalisation, then to psychologists who finally diagnose me with depression, ptsd, emotional dysregulation etc.
iâ€™ve suffered dramatic weight loss, a mental breakdown and experienced some of the hardest decisions iâ€™ve ever had to make. this alongside severe cystic acne, body weight fluctuations, panic attacks, violent outbursts, periods where i black out, and a massive knock on confidence...the whole 9 yards.
iâ€™ve got tattoos that hide scars, iâ€™ve written songs that speak when i canâ€™t. and iâ€™ve written this post over and over again struggling to find the words iâ€™m trying to put across.
itâ€™s been so difficult, i wouldnâ€™t wish this on anyone, and itâ€™s far from over.
i want to take the time to thank each and every one of you who have been here; supporting me and loving me no matter what.
thank you for believing in me and thank you for understanding when nobody else did. 
i am truly grateful for each and every one of you.
a bubbly and cheerful personality paired with a convincing smile can hide a lot.
never take anything or anyone for granted. you truly never know whatâ€™s really going on.
to any abuse or rape victim, it is not your fault, and it never will be. talk about it, get help, donâ€™t do what i do and lock it up inside until the boiling point becomes too much to handle.
you are not alone, and you never will be.
#metoo 
#mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mentalillness 
thank you,
i love you,
ellie.

text:
dear 24. you were a year of discovery. you were a year of hard work. you were a year of sleepless nights. you were a year of laughter and pain. but most importantly you were a year of growth. .

this year god gave me the courage to get out of my comfort zone. i quit my comfortable little job as a supervisor that i had for 6 years. i got an apartment for me and graham. i flew on planes to some of the most amazing places and met some awesome people. i fully embraced my life as a single woman and a single mom â€” which lead to me finding more about who i am in christ. i have seen the beauty and the hardest parts of motherhood. i broke down so many barriers around my heart that years of sexual abuse, depression, anxiety, toxic relationships and friendships, and hurt had built. i got my mind healthy and my heart fixed on god. .

i also learned to be real with everyone. iâ€™m no longer scared to tell my story. iâ€™m no longer ashamed. iâ€™ve received so much grace, love, and forgiveness from an awe inspiring heavenly father. i donâ€™t have a huge following on here, but iâ€™ve still got so many people who are here that have gone through, could go through, or know some one who has gone through the same things. so yes, i am a photographer, but i am also a human with a story. and if my being vulnerable and laying it all out there is going to help at least one person, then thatâ€™s worth it. .

so hereâ€™s to 25. i have no idea what this next year entails, but iâ€™m going into it ready for any opportunities, teachable moments, hard times, or good times. iâ€™m ready because i know this is the path god has intended for me to walk along. he is there during the best and worst of times, and in that i find so much peace. .
that being said, i wish you all the merriest of christmases and the happiest of new years â¤ï¸
.
and if you are struggling please reach out!! whether you need a friend to talk to, pray for you, or simply just to say â€œhey, itâ€™ll be okâ€ reach out. iâ€™m here for you ğŸ–¤

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
winter solstice and the full moon in cancer
.
happy solstice weekend, loves! the darkest night of the year is always a portal, but this one feels especially hinged with the polarity of the full moon bringing matters of fertility and growth to heady culmination. perhaps, like me, you have been sleeping and dreaming and loafing a bit more (even if it was a cold that finally forced me to slow down). .
.
.

the sabian symbol of 0 degrees cancer is that of a ship changing its flag, and we may feel compelled to change tack in some area of our lives this week (look to the houses hosting the luminaries for further clues). the full moonâ€™s sextile to uranus will ensure that any abrupt changes in our habits and routines will go smoothly, and can be integrated without too much turmoil. the moon in cancer is all about those wild mood swings, and with the influence of uranus we may find ourselves jack-knifing between throwing plates, and make-up sexâ€”but all in good fun.
.
.
.
the full moonâ€™s strongest aspect was a schmoopy trine between venus and neptune, softening any capricornian basalt. romance, swooning and enchantment could mark the coming weeks, and perhaps a few surprises in the love department. Â after a couple months of rather abrasive mars aspects to the lunar phases, a bit of vaseline smeared on the lens is a welcome change. yes, weâ€™re all tetchy and battle-scarred, but some soft-focus and candlelit nights this christmas is the universeâ€™s present to you (and donâ€™t look that gift horse in the mouth!). .
.
.
eclipse season will soon be upon us afterall (the next lunation will be a solar eclipse on january 5th), so enjoy this dreamy lacuna while you can. break out the cava. listen to â€œlast christmasâ€ by wham sans irony (ok, that oneâ€™s a big ask). definitely book yourself a trip to a spa, or some roman baths, or one of those massages where youâ€™re floating in water. aire in barcelona will be my gift to myself, with its exposed brick, flickering candles, and salt-water pools - can't recommend it enough! (continued in comments belowâ¬‡)

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the companyâ€™s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when youâ€™re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a personâ€™s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the â€œtraining setâ€ refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your â€œfeature setâ€: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, itâ€™s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data â€“ the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that youâ€™re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
- she [rebekah mercer] loved me. she was like, oh we need more of your type on our side!

your type? - the gays. she loved the gays. so did steve [bannon]. he saw us as early adopters. he figured, if you can get the gays on board, everyone else will follow. itâ€™s why he was so into the whole milo [yiannopoulos] thing.

robert mercer was a pioneer in ai and machine translation. he helped invent algorithmic trading â€“ which replaced hedge fund managers with computer programs â€“ and he listened to wylieâ€™s pitch. it was for a new kind of political message-targeting based on an influential and groundbreaking 2014 paper researched at cambridgeâ€™s psychometrics centre, called: - computer-based personality judgments are more accurate than those made by humans. - in politics, the money man is usually the dumbest person in the room. whereas itâ€™s the opposite way around with mercer, says wylie. - he said very little, but he really listened. he wanted to understand the science. and he wanted proof that it worked.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: iâ€™ve learned how i present myself attracts different types of men. the media promotes us all looking like kardashianâ€™s with lip injections, butt and breast implants and fillers (not to knock anyone who chooses to do those things) but i have watched shows like married with children in the 90s make comments about how a girl dresses too provocatively change to now, women and even preteens, wearing way more provactive outfits on the disney channel and instagram! we as women have a right to feel empowered and it is never an excuse to sexually harass, but we as women have to ask ourselves if we are attracting the type of attention we want by falling into the media pushed agenda to overtly sexualize us? empowerment comes from our hearts and minds, not what we wear. iâ€™ve lived in the middle east and wore full hijab/shayla (head scarf ) and abaya (overcoat) and even niqab (face mask) and iâ€™ve also been an exotic dancer and lingerie model and bikini waitress and dressed very proactively, so i feel like iâ€™ve had experience of all sides of this topic. neither lifestyle made me feel empowered, for different reasons. both gave me a false sense of power based on extremes. using my body to get attention and money left me feeling empty and like no one saw my true worth and value. covering my body completely made me feel like i wasnâ€™t an individual and like as a woman i had to hide myself from men so they wouldnâ€™t sexualize me instead of them practicing respect for women. no disrespect to either lifestyle, these are only my experiences. this venus retrograde really changed my approach to dating and the type of man i want to attract into my life. men attracted primarily to the physical will always seek other women because there is so much beauty in all forms out there and sexualized images of women everywhere they turn. i want a man who can see my unique beauty and mind and soul and the level of love i can offer in all of my expressions. my physical body is such a small and limited part of myself and iâ€™ve watched it change throughout the years and it always will, but the beauty of my heart and soul and love only grows stronger as i evolve and thatâ€™s where my true beauty is.

text:
meet our musical composer, kristin sgarro! @oksgars "there is a lot of content in scar tissue that is wildly relatable to our generationâ€”the kinds of thought processes some of these characters go through are absolutely ones that iâ€™ve also had. reflecting that through music was (and is, as i expand scene-change music into a more expansive soundtrack) its own task, but the characters were certainly the starting point. the theme, for instance, has a pensive quality to it, but it also has this color of constant motion: itâ€™s like learning how to live in anxiety, which jessica certainly struggles with. she, and i, find the moments where the familiar is comfortingâ€” perhaps even soothingâ€”and having those moments alternate with others where she is unable to stop or change the course of action. like a resolved chord, but no end to the music.
i grew up around a lot of rich choral works as well as pop-jazz and -country classics; and i mean everything from nat king cole to billy joel to the eagles and chicago, then throw in some showtunes and add your a cappella arrangements. as i got older, a lot of that didnâ€™t go away, but it evolved into a desire for simple but still lush sounds. if i had an ipod today it would be filled with glen hansard, ingrid michaelson, jamie cullum, sara bareilles, miles davis, john coltraneâ€”and i should really pay mind to some tunes hitting the airwaves these days, because there is some genius happening now. itâ€™s unfortunate how little radio i listen to: for example, i actually have â€œtroye sivanâ€ written down on a post-it note on my desk because the first time i heard it i was so moved that i stopped working and looked up the artist."

meet our musical composer, kristin sgarro! @oksgars "there is a lot of content in scar tissue that is wildly relatable to our generationâ€”the kinds of thought processes some of these characters go through are absolutely ones that iâ€™ve also had. reflecting that through music was (and is, as i expand scene-change music into a more expansive soundtrack) its own task, but the characters were certainly the starting point. the theme, for instance, has a pensive quality to it, but it also has this color of constant motion: itâ€™s like learning how to live in anxiety, which jessica certainly struggles with. she, and i, find the moments where the familiar is comfortingâ€” perhaps even soothingâ€”and having those moments alternate with others where she is unable to stop or change the course of action. like a resolved chord, but no end to the music.
i grew up around a lot of rich choral works as well as pop-jazz and -country classics; and i mean everything from nat king cole to billy joel to the eagles and chicago, then throw in some showtunes and add your a cappella arrangements. as i got older, a lot of that didnâ€™t go away, but it evolved into a desire for simple but still lush sounds. if i had an ipod today it would be filled with glen hansard, ingrid michaelson, jamie cullum, sara bareilles, miles davis, john coltraneâ€”and i should really pay mind to some tunes hitting the airwaves these days, because there is some genius happening now. itâ€™s unfortunate how little radio i listen to: for example, i actually have â€œtroye sivanâ€ written down on a post-it note on my desk because the first time i heard it i was so moved that i stopped working and looked up the artist."

text:
i'm *wildly* devoted to god (i pray every morning before i open my eyes), and i have a fixed love organized religion -- *any* organized religion, though i am a born-again baptist christian, but lately? crosses have been *dropping* out of the sky before me. today, i just looked up and god was just standing there (and sure, it's an illusion bouncing from a window, but no it's not at all, yes it is but no its not..) .

and to some i don't seem "religious" bc i remove god from americanized forms of organized religion, particularly my religion, but i live by a firm and unwavering faith that i *can't* remove myself from, even when i just "don't get" the point. i dont think life is ours to control, so i *always* defer to this little whispering inner voice, bc if i ignore it for instructions from a human? it will wake me up during the night, every night until i just submit. it's *totally* bizarre
.

for most people, especially those in my religious community, devotional practice is tied to a certain sterility, but for me it's not; for me god has been a total liberation, so i don't "live on purpose" or posture a disingenuous kindness, i just do what i think is "right" -- not (man-made, white embodied) god(ly), but just what i think is right, and i do this without exception
.

and i will sue over it
.

i've changed in all ways since my stroke, but this "living by an internal whisper", which i now understand as god, has remained the same since i was just a baby. even my sister, who i've never been close to, used to always say, "if people knew me they would know [me] as a conservative christian" (we were raised atheist) bc i'm very clear about wrong vs. right, but not in the way other people are. an example of this would be my understanding that my ex husband survived us, we didn't survive him. to everyone else its the opposite... right and wrong are in the cracks of "becoming", and i will search the text of a story to asses where the real villain is hiding, which in my marriage was me, naturally. the person i represented was an embodiment of his fears, realized
.

anyway, im really grateful for these small (or huge and in my face) signs like these i've been encountering
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
this is the look of a woman fed up.
this is a woman fighting against her suppressive conditioning, only to be reminded of why she is a non-voluntary shut-in.
this is the look of a woman who finds solace in embracing her true calling, but is constantly reminded as to why she allows herself to be her own worst enemy, but only because she allows herself to be controlled and manipulated mentally by the general suppressive collective.
ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬ğŸ¤¬
being an obnivert with a leo sun with an aquarius rising is a fucking nightmare-- especially with an upbring and conditioning like what i went through. to keep things short, i went a little out of my comfort zone and did a live reading event the other night, but it turned into more of a teaching experiance, and teaching someone about something i love is always going to be easy for me to do and a pure joy.
so. i leave the event and most of everyone else to their shopping. within minutes some old man (i think) on a bench across the street starts screaming these horrible, sexist things. i did my best not to look at them, so i couldn't tell if they were with someone or simply had a stack of possessions piled next to them. so at first i assumed they were arguing with someone, but the more they shrieked, the more i realized they were yelling genetalized, terrible things at me.
"get back into the kitchen and make me a sandwitch!"
"how dare you be out here on your own, strutting."
"how dare you-- what makes you think you have the right to take a life of an innocent child"
stuff like that, becoming more and more erratic and incoherant in their screaming turned shreiking, more incoherent with their rage and blatant disrespect with every "point" they tried to make. i passed a man about my age taking out the trash for one of many downtown establishments. he said that the dude was probably off his rocker and that he would not allow the psycho to touch me. i thanked him and told him that i was on my way to the bus hub. i had almost thirty minutes before my bus left, so i stopped at a bar close by to hide and have a drink to calm my nerves.

in 1935 the group took on the meat packing industry. they burned a huge packing house in protest of high prices, and they joined thousands of chicago housewives in a march that shut down the cityâ€™s entire meat industry. leagues initiated negotiations, boycotts and canvasses locally to convince neighborhood business to hire black employees. leagues began to form all over the country, one in new york, washington, d.c, maryland and ohio. from the local chapters a national housewivesâ€™ league of america was born.

over the years the group educated women on their buying power, and encouraged them to only shop at african-american owned businesses. also, they encouraged the women to patronize the white businesses that employed african-americans. the league celebrated many events such as national housewivesâ€™ day, april national trade month, essay contests and many other events.

freely given.Â consenting is a choice you make without pressure, manipulation, or under the influence of drugs or alcohol.

reversible.Â anyone can change their mind about what they feel like doing, anytime. even if youâ€™ve done it before, and even if youâ€™re both naked in bed.

informed.Â you can only consent to something if you have the full story. for example, if someone says theyâ€™ll use a condom and then they donâ€™t, there isnâ€™t full consent.

enthusiastic.Â when it comes to sex, you should only do stuff you want to do, not things that you feel youâ€™re expected to do.

specific.Â saying yes to one thing (like going to the bedroom to make out) doesnâ€™t mean youâ€™ve said yes to others (like having sex). #nomore #breakingthesilence #timesup #metoo #nomoreapp

text:
holidays can be particularly challenging - and potentially dangerous - for survivors. @rainn offers excellent guidance on protecting yourself and/or loved ones (see link in my profile).
.

if you're struggling, or if you encounter a situation that feels inappropriate and you're not sure how to handle, contact the national sexual assault hotline at 800.656.hope or online chat via rainn.org. it's free, confidential, and open 24/7. .
.
you'll also find additional info on recognizing the signs of child sexual abuse, read about how rainn supports survivors, and more. take care of yourself, and of the ones you love.
.
.

no tree for me this year as i am leaving town soon after the holiday. got these beautiful flowers instead ğŸŒº

we don't need gifts or elaborate fancy dinners to make this time of year special. i used to get so upset comparing my life to others and only saw that i didn't have a husband and children and a big tree and a traditional family of my own. now i see the freedom it provides me, i am going to take a solo trip and do whatever i want! it's so crazy i was upset for so many years when i have such a wonderful life full of opportunity. 
it's taken me years of personal effort , 90 days in rehab and never settling for average to find happiness alone.  it's so priceless that i refuse to let anyone take it from me. i am finally free of this constant voice telling me that i was not good enough. don't let the marketing get to you, we are all good enough. my happiness doesn't depend on my relationship status

text:
ah, storiesâ€¦ everybody loves to hear them, tell them, carry them deep within, all life long. drama, tragedy, grief, happiness, fate: a thing of beauty is a joy forever.
.
renaissance artists knew this and, more than any other, ovidâ€™s metamorphoses were a rich source of inspiration to them. yes, those days the old roman poet was alive and kicking! titian, leonardo, berniniâ€¦ their names are linked forever to ovidâ€™s apollo and daphne, diana and actaeon, orpheus and eurydice, to name but a few.
.
the lady in the painting above is called arachne. her story is simple (all good stories are): as she was an extremely talented weaver she challenged athena to a weaving contest â€“ not before denying she owed her skills to this goddess though. not a brilliant idea. whatâ€™s worse: arachne wins (with a weaving, btw, depicting zeus misleading and seducing mortal women, - letâ€™s say #metoo 100bc). so finally â€“ a goddess has to do something in those kinds of situations - athena turns her into a spider: â€œshe sprinkled her with poison, arachne's hair fell out. with it went her nose and ears, her head shrank to the smallest size, and her whole body became tiny. her slender fingers stuck to her sides as legs, the rest is belly, from which she still spins a thread, and, as a spider, weaves her ancient web.â€ bugger. doesnâ€™t sound too nice.
.
jealousy, hatred, revengeâ€¦ - these are the ingredients of a good story. take them, put them in a pot, let boil for couple of hours, and there it is. if youâ€™re lucky of course. fascinating to see, btw, how in early b&w movies the bad guy was the one lurking behind the corner, pulling faces, almost drooling revenge. clear times. in the painting above thereâ€™s more subtlety: this modern painter chooses to picture, instead of plain hatred, calm self esteem and conscious pride, - maybe with a tiny pinch of ambition and challenge: the sugar on the cake. refined and delicate. human.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
truth bomb time:
i woke up this morning to a barrage of angry texts with cursing, calling me an idiot, even the middle finger emoji.
ã€°ï¸
sadly itâ€™s all over me asking my ex to keep our son a couple extra hours today so i can get us ready for our early flight tomorrow.
because i spent the whole week in the hospital with said 5-yr-old.
i acknowledge we all handle stress differently.
ã€°ï¸
one of my new year intentions is to detach from the habitual rotation of hurt and anger that leads to me feeling victimized by the emotional abuse that was our marriage.
it seeped out from me and i lost a lot of friends due to my lashing out from the darkness.
we hid it well.
until the end.
ã€°ï¸
funny thing about this is that iâ€™m the happiest now than iâ€™ve been in a very long time.
yes.
iâ€™m still mourning who and what i thought the person i spent almost 10yrs with was.
i grieve not being around my son for 50% of his life due to joint custody.
but
i accept the ex is no longer the same person.
maybe he was never who i thought he was.
i accept i am no longer the desperate, substances to numb, codependent self that i was.
ã€°ï¸
affirmation: this time â€œaloneâ€ is medicine to heal.
ã€°ï¸
i move forward.
i lean into the love of family and friends
while learning that i am enough.
they are enough.
a relationship does not define me.
i define me.
my faith and spiritual practice define me.

text:
last week i spoke at an event focused on #metoo and the church. even though i speak in front of people often, i had a whole other feeling of discomfort. i wrestled with feeling like i was an imposter- why do they want to hear from me???- amongst other things. at the end of the day though, i made a choice to be brave, show up, and do my best. but oh the wrestling to get there... more on it in my bbravecoaching blog this week. link in bio.

*

text:
"ladkiyon ko ghar se door nahi jaana chahiye" is as baseless as "tough guys never cry"!! these are merely stereotypical mindset. naming a few indian women who stepped out of their home and made a mark in history making mockery of "ladkiyon ko ghar se door nahi jaana chahiye"...
- pratibha devisingh patil : the first woman president of india - sarojini naidu : the first lady governor of an indian state.
- sucheta kripalani : the first lady chief minister of an indian state. - vijayalaxmi pandit : the first woman president of un general assembly.
- cornelia sorabjee : the first woman advocate of india.
- justice leila seth : the first woman to be appointed chief justiceÂ of a state high court. - justice m fatima beevi :  the first woman to be appointed judge of the supreme court of india.

text:
last night, a fellow survivor reached out to me and asked me if i had any advice for handling the emotional impact of rape. oof. isnâ€™t that the question?? i live every second of every minute of every hour of every day asking this of myself. itâ€™s a lot. and itâ€™s not easy. but i do have some answers! first of all, let me be clear- i am not a mental health professional. i myself see a licensed clinical social worker weekly, and that is absolutely *essential* to my wellbeing. i also keep a shortlist of contact info of some trusted individuals i know i can reach out to if i am in crisis, and i suggest you do the same. (if you are a survivor and have not sought professional mental health treatment, i highly recommend it. see the resources in my highlights if you need some information to start.) that being said, the first thing i do for myself is journal. if youâ€™re having trouble getting started with that, just write affirmations- over and over. write kind words to yourself, even if you donâ€™t believe them yet. write what you wish you or someone you love would say to you. surround yourself with positive words. when you find yourself getting stuck in cycles of negative self-talk, repeat these affirmations. my username is an affirmation! i call this account @bossladycreates because my artwork makes me feel like a boss. the first word in my bio is badass because thatâ€™s what i am. the more i see it and the more i say it, the more i believe it. â€¢ 
dealing with the emotional impact of rape- even day to day- is not easy. and healing is not linear. but be kind and gentle to yourself. reach out. talk about what happened. (if youâ€™re not comfortable talking about it directly, write it down somewhere private. submit it anonymously. get it out.) ask for help. bad days are okay because there will be better ones. âœ¨ğŸŒ± click the link in my bio if you would like to contribute your story to the survivor tree project. #survivor #survivoradvocate #survivorselfcare #cptsd #ptsd #mentalhealthawareness #believesurvivors #believewomen #believeblackwomen #rapesurvivor #metoo #timesup #endrapeculture #metoomovement

text: i wonder what rowan county really does with this money? what the person hired into the job position actually does? because anyone thatâ€™s been a victim in the rowan county courtroom knows that none of these services are extended to the victim.  instead, the da has no contact with the victim until minutes before the case and only after the da had communicated with the person being charged. for example: in one case the abuser claimed that the victim had a â€œhistoryâ€ of suicide attempts and had an audio recording of her threatening suicide the day of the assault in question. the reality was that the victim had eaten a bottle of tylenol when 14 years old, some 20 plus years earlier and there was no other history of suicide attempts nor any history of mental illness. the audio recording was of someone else completely. the victim also had acquired a recording of the assault in question that clearly showed what happened. however the victim was never given the opportunity to mention these things to the da until after the da dismissed the case! in another case withthe same victim and abuser, the abuser was found guilty and appealed it to a jury trial. however, despite the victim making multiple calls to the clerk of court in an attempt to find out when the court date would be, and the assurance from the da that it would be scheduled at least two weeks in advance, the case ended up being dismissed. the da office made one phone call from an out of state cell phone to inform victim of the court date but hung up when the victim didnâ€™t answer (victim didnâ€™t answer cause number was from same state as abusers former telephone number). a subpoena was then issued and deputies came to the home one time but found no one home. due to the rural location they did not return. victim was told by clerk of court the case was on â€œstandbyâ€ and victim would be contacted for day she needed to come to the court. instead no one made any attempts to let her know and the da dismissed the case while the victim was waiting to know what date the case would be tried.  the da acts with no concern for the victim and is the reason #metoo exists #rowancounty #nc #court

text:
this is not the post i had planned for today but this girl needs to get stuff off her chest so here we go! if you want to hear me talk about women in the workplace, sexual harassment, & a little bit of my story keep reading! if youâ€™re here for the fun happy posts then keep scrolling. ğŸ’¼
i am a chef which means i work in a kitchen with majorly men every day. kitchens are very tough, vulgar environments they have taught me to be a tough cookie & get along with guys really well because for the most part thatâ€™s who i work with. at every restaurant or kitchen iâ€™ve worked in i have been sexually harassed, itâ€™s pretty much to be expected in my field of work... does that make it okay? no. have i gotten used to it? yes. comments, jokes, and nicknames have been made based on my appearance & iâ€™ve been extremely uncomfortable but learned to brush it off because the last thing i would want to do is ruin someoneâ€™s career. how backwards is that thinking??? society has made me believe that i should suffer the attention and not report such things because someone could loose their job over my discomfort. within the past week i have endured more than any person should have to & with the support from my friends i reported my superior yesterday for not only sexual harassment but sexual assault as well. was it easy? heck no. was it the right thing to do? absolutely! i talked to so many people in my life about the incident and what did i get from the women, nothing but encouraging words of support: â€œyou need to report it, he could loose his job for that!â€ but what did i get from the men i told: â€œoh donâ€™t tell anyone what happened, he could loose his job for that.â€ iâ€™m not sure what will happen to him honestly but what i do know is that it is not my problem. i am safe and i feel protected after telling my bosses. so as a victim of multiple sexual assaults & loads of sexual harassment i am here for you, you are heard, speak up, report any and everything, and most importantly it is not your fault.ğŸ’› #metoo
*i am not looking for pitty or sympathy so please leave that at the door ğŸ˜Š

text:
some are born in it
some sweat it out
whatever the reason
i am where i am 
i am who i am
i own it

who are you to enter
my territory
and not pay your dues
you think you can fly high
with the fuel that's inside you
open your eyes
i'm the only fuel
that can propel you (to new tomorrows)
(to new horizons)
(to new milestones)
(to the next day)

you can't afford
to run out of me
can you?

i'm the benevolent being
and you have caught my attention
consider yourself lucky
to be my interest today (what have you got for me?)
(what lies underneath that skin?)
(what can you learn from me?)
(how long will you take to begin?) kneel down and let's roll over

in satin sheets,
on crowded streets,
in midnight meets

kneel down 
i won't repeat

take me higher and you'll
get higher too

it doesn't matter if
you dare blurt your sob story
screaming #metoo

i'm here to drink fine wine
and so can you
just take my hand
and do what i tell you to

#poems #poem #poemsofinstagram #poemsforher #poemsforhim #spilledink #poetsofindia #poetsofig #poetryisnotdead #instapoem #love #poetry #poetrycommunity #poetryofinstagram

text:
2018 was voor mij, afgezien van een paar lichtpunten en mijn verhuizing naar kenia, een waar rampjaar. alles kwam tot een dieptepunt op het moment dat ik een aantal maanden geleden verkracht werd. verkracht, zei je? ja, verkracht. â€œdat moet je niet op instagram zetten, lot,â€ waarschuwde een vriendin me gisteren nog. â€œdat is privÃ©.â€ privÃ©, mâ€™n bolle reet. ik bepaal gelukkig zelf wat ik wel en niet met de wereld deel, en ik had en heb nog altijd niets om me voor te schamen â€” want ik heb niets fout gedaan. iets waar ik vanaf het moment dat het gebeurde tot nu gelukkig bÃ­jna geen twijfel over heb gehad. ik heb aan het hele gebeuren ptss overgehouden en zit momenteel nog midden in het verwerkingsproces. morgen begin ik met emdr-therapie, waarbij je de herinnering aan een trauma aan een psycholoog vertelt en die je ondertussen afleidt met â€œafleidende stimulansenâ€.
.
voor vice heb ik over de meest privÃ© aspecten van mijn leven geschreven. het interesseerde me geen bal dat iedereen en zijn moeder met een paar klikken extreem intieme details over mijn leven te weten kon komen. waarom niet? omdat ik aan het aantal berichten in mijn inbox zag dat mensen met soortgelijke ervaringen baat hadden bij mijn openheid. â€œdoor jouw verhaal heb ik eindelijk kunnen erkennen dat ik anorexia heb.â€ â€œik laat jouw artikelen tijdens mijn opname aan mijn vrienden en familie lezen, zodat ze begrijpen wat er in mijn hoofd omgaat.â€
.
toch was het dit keer anders. omdat het nog maar zo kort geleden gebeurd is. omdat ik geen juridische stappen tegen de dader kan ondernemen. en omdat ik toch ergens een schuldgevoel voel branden; zoals het geval is voor bijna iedereen die slachtoffer is geweest van seksueel geweld. had ik maar niet zoveel gedronken. had ik maar beter teruggevochten. had ik maar beter op mijn drankje gelet in die club. had ik maar...
.
zelf heb ik veel gehad aan alle dappere vrouwen (en anderen) die n.a.v. de #metoo-beweging hun verhaal hebben durven doen. en ik hoop daar nu ook mijn steentje aan bij te dragen. mijn inbox staat in ieder geval altijd open, mocht je behoefte hebben om te praten. take care mensen, en let alsjeblieft op elkaar. â¤ï¸ op naar betere tijden.

text:
i read a piece by #tishanidoshi on #granta. she talks about her unpleasant experiences with #anandjon, the indian designer who is now in prison in the u.s since he was accused by numerous women of sexual harassment, way before #metoo. 
i have an anand jon story although thankfully not a #metoo one. i've never met him. way back during the turn of the millennium, when i was a freelance journalist, i received a press release about him from an unknown sender. i didn't write that particular story, but i forwarded the release to my editor, who assigned the story to someone else. 
a couple of years later, i contacted him myself for an interview with madras plus. i wasn't "assigned" the article, but i wrote it and then pitched it to madras plus after which it was published and i was paid. anand jon was accessible throughout the interview via email.

it was after several years that i got to know about the number of girls who complained about him. by then, he and his sister were on my facebook. i had never met him or interacted with him, but here was someone i had interviewed, who was in jail! that was a first for me! 
last year, when i decluttered my facebook list, they went too. talking about #anandjon, i believe he studied in don bosco in chennai. at the age of 18, i knew several boys from don bosco myself, who i have wished for years that i could 'un-know'. not saying the school is bad or anything, just that i have met some unsavoury people who, i bet, knew him. 
instead of pasting my interview with anand jon here, i'd like to popularize tisha's article in granta. read it!

text:
with festivities comes a lot of blessings, beautiful experiences, brightening up the house, ethnicity but yes with little ones in the house, the mess cannot be ignored.
thankfully we have something natural in the form of #huggieswipes, a quick cleaning solution for my champ. 
having the extract from cucumber and aloe vera, huggies baby wipes, not just keeps the baby's skin nourished but also has mild yet nice fragrance. they are clinically tested to be safe and gentle and are paraben free too. not at all sticky, it quickly wipes off the mess.

do give them a try and go green this festive season!! .

-
"bob collins"
â€¢ 5cl gin
â€¢ 2cl lime juice
â€¢ 2cl elderflower syrup
â€¢ juniper berries
â€¢ cucumber
â€¢ 7-8 oregano leaves
â€¢ soda
-

â€¢ shake and pour into a collins glass with ice and cucumber strips
â€¢ drop in the rest of the juniper berries
â€¢ top off with soda
â€¢ garnish with a fresh oregano sprig
-

text:
i thought i was actually going to ok for a while. that only lasted a day. now i'm back to only wanting to sleep and not even trying to eat. i don't even really know what happened. yesterday was just kind of filled with bad memories and just overall bad feelings. we had taken my sister's boyfriend to get his hair cut and then went to the mall for her birthday. the ride to the salon and during the haircut i felt fine only a little anxious because the salon was a bit small for everyone and i felt in the way since i wasn't even there to get anything done. then during the ride to the mall i realised my sister's boyfriend kind of smelled like how my abuser did. or at least how i remember him smelling. after realizing that i just felt so uncomfortable and kind of wanted to tell my mom but i don't know what she could have done. my mom and i went off to do our own stuff at the mall while my sister and her boyfriend went to find some clothes. i wanted some ice cream so my mom and i got some but when i was eating it i felt like everyone was looking at me or watching me. at that point i just wanted to go home and sleep. i don't really know what i'm doing anymore. i have to at least pretend to be better since christmas is in a few days but even that feels like too much. i just want the holidays to be over and for my sister to go away.

#depression #depressed #anxiety #socialanxiety #sucidalthoughts #suicide #suicidal #eatingdisorders #family #selfharm #cutting #holiday #holidays #hopeless #givingup #goaway #metoo #sexualabuse #sexualassault

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
#williamshatner says #metoo movement not considering context...
in an interview with dailymailtv, the 87-year-old shatner said he felt that the #metoo movement is taking some things out of context.
â€œbut if you look back at things that were written and said 20, 30 years ago, itâ€™s a different context,â€ shatner said. â€œand youâ€™ve got to judge it by that context. rape and pillage, absolutely not, those are crimes against humanity. but saying â€˜would you make love with me?â€™ and the opposing party says yes or no, i canâ€™t fathom whatâ€™s wrong with that.
â€œitâ€™s like saying would you have dinner, would you like to write a song with me, would you do an interview? iâ€™m not insulted by you asking me to do an interview. maybe itâ€™s my mindset based on the years iâ€™ve lived, but iâ€™m trying to be fair and i donâ€™t see the problem.â€
shatner did praise the movement for exposing hidden harassment in the entertainment business. â€œin 2018, we have the #metoo movement, which i think is great, that these hidden forces are exposed and not to be allowed and women have equal rights,â€ shatner said. â€œiâ€™ve got three daughters, iâ€™m all for that.â€
he also suggested that the â€œfirebrandsâ€ who have led the movement should step away and let more â€œbusiness-like peopleâ€ take over as spokespeople.
â€œiâ€™ve got three daughters and iâ€™m glad that they have more opportunity,â€ he said. â€œat the same time, itâ€™s become hysterical. itâ€™s a whole new culture. the whole business has changed. the whole man-woman relationship has changed to a severe degree.â€ criticized later on social media for being out of touch, shatner refused to back down.

text:
weep, woman. weep for all your sons and for all your brothers who have lost their way.

bleed, woman. bleed for the souls that have dived into darkness. let your blood spill on their hands.

stand, woman. stand from the dirt they have thrown you into. rise to your nature and reach elegantly upwards like the flower that blooms in defiance of the ugly.

speak, woman. speak out the pain you carry. your biggest shame is not in the acts done unto you, but in the silence that you keep.

dance, woman. swing towards the light and connect to the wisdom of your heart. celebrate in your power for only the weak will harm you.

shine, woman. shine the light that guide your daughters and your sisters. let your fire give birth to love, the love that will save you, the love that saves us all.
_
a letter to all the females who are currently being sexually assaulted.

nepal. december 2018. full moon. 
_

text:
this is one of my more recent pieces that helped me come to terms with my own journey and the reason i believe in the movements hash-tagged below. this is the best way i could visually represent and abstract the feelings i've experienced when women from all backgrounds - religious to new age to buddhist - have spoken against me using my voice to share that i do this because my pain and my story is sadly shared by more than 1 in 3 women now. i made this because i believe women were designed to be each other's biggest cheerleaders, most faithful and unconditionally loving friends, and supporters who will love each other enough to say hard things even if that means losing a relationship, for the sake of acting on the proverb "faithful are the wounds of a friend." i believe that when one sister takes medicine for the migraine that kept her home from work , but criticizes her sister for taking the medication that prevents the kind of headache that keeps you in a mental hospital, words cut like glass shards in the soul and heart. i believe that when women create incredible movements like the ones listed below but value being right over respecting their other sisters and #risingtogether, actions cut like glass shards to the heart and soul. but, those very same opinions and actions can be redeemed and turned to sought-after precious shards of sea glass. and when we let that sea glass be our lens- then and then only- will these movements succeed. may we always value our sister in every necessary way over just seeking to be right.

text:
most mainstream wellness/self-help/healing/spirituality/coaching spaces perpetuate ableism in their failure to relate sensitively to those living with trauma and mental illness.

looking at this meme, i almost want to laugh... i mean, itâ€™s laughable right? the way that so many people talk about healingâ€”in a manner that dismisses and discounts the terrifying triggers that haunt you when living with traumatic stress.

as i move through the process of understanding and treating my own complex ptsd, i find myself simultaneously and not-so-coincidentally working to heal the psychological damage caused by these wellness spaces and by the corresponding dogma of new age thought and the law of attraction.

the new age asserts that we are somehow each responsible for individually â€œmanifestingâ€ every inch of our lives and our reality. it is the belief that we serve as an â€œenergetic matchâ€ for any experience we attract into our lives and an insistence that the conditions of our lives are only ever responding to our individual thoughts/internal state/morality/vibrational frequency.

the law of attraction is traumatizing in and of itself; it causes us to rupture, as parts of ourselves are elevated and others exiled in order to fit into a standard of â€œrightousnessâ€ and/or â€œgoodness.â€ we abandon how we authentically experience life in lieu of curating, controlling, and manipulating our field so as to only give space to the clean/light/pure parts of life.

not only this is not how trauma deserves to be attended to, but itâ€™s not how reality works. placing the burden of responsibility on the shoulders of the one whoâ€™s suffering is a violent philosophy that cultivates low empathy in people eager to gaslight, rationalize abuse, and victim blame survivors.

i donâ€™t listen to that garbage anymore.

not only this is not how trauma deserves to be attended to, but itâ€™s not how reality works. placing the burden of responsibility on the shoulders of the one whoâ€™s suffering is a violent philosophy that cultivates low empathy in people eager to gaslight, rationalize abuse, and victim blame survivors.

i donâ€™t listen to that garbage anymore.

text:
please read below. @jessicayellin brings such deep knowledge to what the government shutdown means for the violence against women act, which will also be shut down. â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€”â€” the violence against women act (vawa) was a landmark piece of legislation passed after anita hillâ€™s 1994 testimony at the clarence thomas hearings. this weekend, congress allowed funding for vawa to expire, a casualty of the government shutdown fight. Â°

the law funds programs that help victims of intimate partner violence and sexual assault. for example vawa supports: - rape-crisis centers and hotlines
- building community programs to combat abuse
- legal aid for survivors
- funds to help prosecute attackers
- it revised restitution and sentencing for violent crimes, typically against domestic partners
- it provides this support for undocumented immigrants, lgbtq individuals and native americansÂ°

the decision to let vawa lapse was no accident. in july rep. sheila jackson lee (d, tx) introduced a bill to reauthorize vawa (meaning: extend funding long-term). it included new measures like expanded gun control laws and housing for victims of domestic violence and stalking. it got limited  republican support. twice congress temporarily extended funding â€”  until sept 30, dec 7. then they folded a resolution to extend the act until feb into the big spending bill. that failed when the government shutdown. Â°

dem rep. joe kennedy tweeted â€œgop & @realdonaldtrump arenâ€™t only shutting down the government tonight, theyâ€™re allowing the violence against women act to expire and leaving survivors of domestic violence & sexual assault without critical, lifesaving resources. shameful.â€Â° bottom line: vawa is funded by both the department of justice, which shut down, and health and human services, which is still up and running. so some programs will continue to receive funding through hhs.  vawa has been allowed to expire in the past (from 2011-2013). we expect the program will be funded again when democrats take control of the house in january, provided they make it a priority.

text: five days after surgery and recovering at my parents home, i came back to st. paul to be photographed by the @startribune and the other survivors who shared their stories in the denied justice series. there was no way i was going to miss this opportunity, especially given that my surgery was directly related to my experiences with sexual assault. i am once again, grateful for the platform that was given to us, but am also feeling betrayed by a government that has allowed the violence against women act to expire because of the childish machinations of a worthless president. women matter and our voices matter. the lives of the oppressed, and forgotten and abused matter. my heart goes out to all women, trans individuals, non-binary and those with marginalized genders and identities. we will make certain that our voices are heard. #insta #instagram #instapic #chicana #chingona #mexicana #latinx #feminist #intersectionalfeminism #bruja #brujasofinstagram #feminista #startribune #deniedjustice #violenceagainstwomen #government #governmentshutdown #fucktrump #notmypresident #metoo #women #womenempowerment #socialjustice #activism #advocate #socialjusticewarrior #feminista

text:
2018 has been rough, guys. in april a repressed memory of childhood rape ripped through my subconscious, landing centerstage in my mind. iâ€™ve had numerous experiences with sexual assault in my twenties, all of them more minor; but this memory from my childhood was not minor. it shed a painful light on why iâ€™ve reacted with such intensity to the â€œromanticâ€ experiences that have made up my adult years. i see with painful lucidity why iâ€™ve been the brand of dysfunctional iâ€™ve been. ğŸ¦‹ 
it was excruciating to accept that this happened to me as a child, but it was somehow worse to mourn what my life could have been. imagine that you live in a lush garden. you thought you knew it well, you were its caretaker after all. then one day a mine explodes. it opens a deep chasm in the garden and sets fire to every beauty you had ever tended. you canâ€™t react to this as an adult would, you can only lie down, cry, and shake like a frightened child. after the smoke clears your eyes open. you can see how the mine was there all along, and how you mistook the noxious effect it had on your garden for normalcy. this is, more or less, how itâ€™s felt to walk this path. ğŸ¦‹ 
lately though, iâ€™ve been making progress. iâ€™m starting to see glimpses of wholeness in myself, and iâ€™m beginning to see the woman iâ€™m becoming. her way of life, unfettered by old fears, intimidates me as much as it thrills me. she feels like love, i think. a new, divine, almost glaring love. ğŸ¦‹ 
iâ€™m grateful to finally taste healing, and for the ways iâ€™ve been guided up to this point. my situation uniquely allows me to share this. my perpetrator, a friend of the family, has been dead for over a decade. in october of 2017, before the memory resurfaced, i felt moved to create a resource for mormon women who are seeking healing after sexual assault. we launched the project, @onsovereignwings in september. i hope it can be half as helpful to you as it has been to me. it would be so meaningful if you could support us! my team is producing some beautiful content, and itâ€™s our sincere hope that we can connect with women whose hearts need healing and stories need voicing. thank you. #metoo ğŸ¦‹

text:
what a year! 
fighting for women's right to choose north and south, fighting for equal marriage, an irish language act, palestinian solidarity activities, celebrating and building on the legacy of '68, delivering thousands of newsletters, having hundreds of conversations, providing assistance to people right across the city, fighting along side #metoo and #ibelieveher movement, standing with workers on strike, fighting to improve and save our health services north and south, campaigning to end austerity, raise awareness of ill mental health, raising our voices and celebrating may day, fighting and will continue to fight to have welfare reforms scrapped, resisting the privatisation of our public services, north and south fighting for housing rights, marched to demand justice for bloody sunday victims, marched with paul's campaign, anti-war demos, resisting the far right, defending refugees and immigrants and demanding an end to internment ... that is just a snapshot of the year, it would be impossible to list it all. every action, every campaign, every set back and victory. but a day didn't pass when we weren't organising to amplify the voice of the working class. 
all the progress made in the past year has been a result of people powered movements.  it's true for progress made every year. 
people not "great" leaders bring change. solidarity not hate, hope not fear powers the change that improves our lives. that's what i want to share from 2018.

a people powered movement can stop welfare reforms, save our environment, it can end discrimination, inequalities and injustices, it can build a society more equal, kinder and fairer. 
merry christmas !

text:
this is not my typical selfie, as you can see. i didn't even make sure i had lipstick on. ğŸ¤· my eyes are raw and my nose is running, but my heart is overflowing. 
i woke up today full of self-loathing. there was that voice...you know, that voice ğŸ“¢ ...asking me how i could have failed again. how can the "health coach" be such a mess? 
the last two days have been fueled with sugar, carbs, caffeine, and more sugar. i kept telling myself that it's no big deal, it's the holidays, it's a birthday, it's whatever.... while all the while knowing that i am lying to myself and completely disregarding all the things i've learned about myself through my years of struggle. i've always envied people like my husband who can get full and then just stop eating. or see a plate of goodies and know they're just not his favorite, so he skips them. that's just not me. that's not my story. 
and i control this so well so much of the time! i've got some great tools, an amazing program i'm blessed to share with others, and 30 years of practice. 
but when life gets really heavy, i mean really heavy...and i'm reminded of things in my past that i have tried to push down (#metoo friends, me too), i often find that my closest ally is only a dollar menu away. 
today though, i pushed back against the siren call of sugar and instead decided to feel what i was pushing against. to feel the pain and the anger and the frustration of things that were done to me without my permission. the pain of being abused once, and then again, and then again. the anger of being told that i had to forgive. the frustration of loving a person and hating them at the same time. and the lies i told myself,  firmly believing in my own heart that if i just pretended it didn't happen, i would be free. .

text:
happy s o l s t i c e & 
f u l l  m o o n!!
as this year comes to a close, we are given this last full moon in cancer. itâ€™s been a year since we have had a full moon in cancer. 
so much has happened during that time...
â€¢
storms. fires. floods. corruption. injustice. 
so many things to look back upon and be glad itâ€™s over. but letâ€™s be careful here, dear ones. donâ€™t leave any of your personal power behind. let the gift within the challenges be illuminated by this full moon. take with you the lessons learned. the wisdom gained. allow yourself to move on without the guilt, regret, shame and blame. use this full moon time to transmute that negative karmic energy. give it to mother earth. it is not yours any longer.
â€¢
some beautiful things happened this year too. precious humans were born into loving homes. more woman and poc representing in political office. #timesup & #metoo and so much more. 
most importantly, we survived the aforementioned chaos! be grateful for how far youâ€™ve already come...
â€¢
now think seriously about what you wish to accomplish in the coming year. itâ€™s time to invest in ourselves! 
what do you need? 
what are you afraid of? 
what tools and resources do you already have that will continue to support you? 
show gratitude. gratitude. gratitude. to yourself and to the universe.
â€¢
remember, you are loved. shine bright, like a diamond. ğŸ’
.
.
.

text:
i had so much fun over the past few (far too short) days visiting family and friends. luckily iâ€™ll be back and forth between brooklyn and boston a lot over the next week so the good times can keep on rollingğŸ˜‹ 
looking forward to a new year with new opportunities to pursue my art in a city iâ€™ve only dreamed of one day being able to live in. my biggest goals moving forward, as a young actor, is to continue to create art that inspires me and i feel passionate about and can give a voice to those who have been silenced or are under or misrepresented in society so that their stories can really be told with the respect that they deserve and i feel so fortunate to be able to work with @wespeakaboutit during this critical time in our history to provide resources for survivors share information with students about how they can look out for themselves, friends, partners, or even strangers and and be a part of this amazing culture change that the #metoo movement has helped destigmatize. the other goal is to create art that can bring a smile to peopleâ€™s faces, because letâ€™s face it, i think we all need a good laugh.

with so many goals and plans, i have to challenge myself to appreciate everything thatâ€™s happening right now. enjoying the journey, connecting with those around me and embracing my own feelings, fears, desires and not dismissing them. i hope that we are all able to take a moment and reflect on how much weâ€™ve accomplished up until this point and to notice all of the beautiful things in our lives and really appreciate how fortunate we are. i canâ€™t wait to see what we all do next. until then, spread your positivity and be open to receive it from others, embrace the mess  because weâ€™re all messy and realize that thereâ€™s something to learn from every experience we have and most importantly, remember that we get to choose how we make people feel through our actions every single day and even the slightest kindness can mean so much.

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the companyâ€™s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when youâ€™re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a personâ€™s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the â€œtraining setâ€ refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your â€œfeature setâ€: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, itâ€™s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data â€“ the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that youâ€™re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian
